node.text: “This may be a game or some sort of political power grab by the Democrats, but we are all going to pay the cost whether you’re a Democrat, Republican or Independent, in terms of public safety.”

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sean Hannity on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'TRUCK DRIVER JOE? Photo Hannity'.

node.text: While visiting a Mack Truck facility, President Biden claimed that he "used to drive an 18-wheeler." There is no evidence that Biden, who has worked in politics for 48 years, ever worked as a truck driver. We’ll show you Biden’s latest blunders and get reactions from Ari Fleischer and Charlie Hurt TONIGHT on “Hannity.”

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sean Hannity on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Hannity MUST-READ QUOTE "Hunter Biden has gone far too long without being held accountable for his actions. That's why I've introduced the PAINTER Act demand transparency from the Bidens and the White House to get to the bottom of who is partaking in his secretive art deals & why.' REP. MICHAEL WALTZ @MichaelGWaltz FOX Û NEWS channel'.

node.text: Rep. Michael Waltz has just introduced legislation that would require transparency from the families of the president and vice president. If passed, the legislation could potentially uncover the identities of the anonymous buyers of Hunter Biden’s art. Many believe that the president’s son is selling influence through his art deals. TONIGHT on “Hannity,” Rep. Waltz will explain his legislation and Lara Trump will discuss the Biden family’s ongoing corruption.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sean Hannity on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text: The CDC recently revised its mask guidelines, but has yet to release the data behind its decision. What’s stopping them from giving the public more information? The CDC is already being accused of playing politics, and it’s been criticized for its lack of transparency. TONIGHT on “Hannity,” Dr. Nicole Saphier and Dr. Janette Nesheiwat will discuss the new mask guidelines.
